  "doc_id": "14236",
  "text": "A nomograph is defined as three or more axes, or scales, arranged such that problems of three or more variables can be solved using a straightedge. In the particular case of EGTs, a nomograph can be constructed using three or more vertical parallel axes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Traditionally, the velocity ratio is used to study the velocity relations among the different links of an EGT [CITATION_3] .",
